No. 63.Isaac C. Lowe v. J. H. Galbraith.Hnder rule fourteen of this court, the assignment of errors must be written upon or attached to the record, and the appellant or plaintiff in error shall in all cases assign errors at the time of filing his record in this court, and on failing to do so, the case may he dismissed. Writ of error dismissed for a failure to comply with this rule.

Judge below, John Keen, Jb.

Attorneys, for appellant, Mr. II. Tompkins ;for ajipellee, Messrs. George & Bunch.Opinion filed April 15, 1886.

Opinion Per Curiam.
